1
00:01:00,480 --> 00:01:01,360
How is the lamb?

2
00:01:01,720 --> 00:01:03,380
This lamb has a heart problem.

3
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:05,880
Grandpa Bate has been keeping it as a pet.

4
00:01:06,240 --> 00:01:08,120
This afternoon, while eating grass,

5
00:01:08,120 --> 00:01:09,440
it had a sudden heart attack

6
00:01:09,440 --> 00:01:10,880
and collapsed on the road.

7
00:01:10,880 --> 00:01:12,520
Several of Grandpa Bate's sheep

8
00:01:12,520 --> 00:01:14,160
have already fallen ill this year.

9
00:01:14,160 --> 00:01:16,080
They are so thin, just skin and bones.

10
00:01:16,080 --> 00:01:18,280
Then they won't sell for much.

11
00:01:18,720 --> 00:01:21,000
Without money, he can't buy new lambs.

12
00:01:21,600 --> 00:01:23,260
Next year will be even harder.

13
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:25,880
It's fine.

14
00:01:26,039 --> 00:01:28,200
Let's walk around the village and take a look.

15
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:29,640
Since we're going to do e-commerce live streaming,

16
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:31,760
let's revitalize everything.

17
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:33,000
If we can't sell mutton,

18
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:33,930
we can sell wool.

19
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:38,400
No construction without destruction.

20
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:40,720
My car is here.

21
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:43,800
Well,

22
00:01:44,120 --> 00:01:45,039
I'm off.

23
00:01:45,240 --> 00:01:47,120
You guys take your time finding treasures here.

24
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:47,759
Okay.

25
00:01:48,759 --> 00:01:49,400
Goodbye, Mr. Yin.

26
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:50,400
Goodbye! Take care, Father Yin.

27
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:51,160
Stay safe.

28
00:01:51,240 --> 00:01:51,960
Alright.

29
00:01:53,240 --> 00:01:54,280
Where did you say we were going?

30
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,120
Let's go now.

31
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:56,600
To Aunt Guli's farmland.

32
00:01:56,960 --> 00:01:57,960
What's there?

33
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:02,160
Goji berries.

34
00:02:11,880 --> 00:02:12,960
This is actually my first time seeing

35
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:14,090
fresh goji berries.

36
00:02:14,160 --> 00:02:14,920
Right?

37
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:16,680
The dried goji berries in your hand

38
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:18,120
are from the first harvest.

39
00:02:18,120 --> 00:02:19,120
At the end of this month,

40
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:21,850
it will be time for the second goji berry harvest.

41
00:02:22,079 --> 00:02:22,720
Look.

42
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:25,040
These red ones

43
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:26,040
are ripe.

44
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:27,400
The ones with a bit of yellow

45
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:28,320
are semi-ripe.

46
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:30,040
Let me pick a red one for you to see.

47
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:31,100
Here, have a taste.

48
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:35,120
It has a grainy texture,

49
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:36,280
and a very sweet aftertaste.

50
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:37,000
Right?

51
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:39,079
The fresh berries have a strong flavor,

52
00:02:39,079 --> 00:02:41,320
much richer than other fruits.

53
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:44,079
But the skin is too thin.

54
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:46,600
At most, they can only be transported

55
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:48,200
to nearby farmers' markets.

56
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:49,720
Even if we plant them

57
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:51,000
around big cities,

58
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:53,280
the transportation and packaging costs

59
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:54,240
would be extremely high.

60
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:55,800
But dried Xinjiang goji berries

61
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,260
shouldn't be hard to sell.

62
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:58,680
They are not hard to sell.

63
00:02:58,720 --> 00:02:59,440
But

64
00:02:59,560 --> 00:03:01,400
the prices of dried goji berries are all about the same.

65
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:02,860
The added value is too low.

66
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:04,860
In our village,

67
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:06,800
the village committee established a cooperative.

68
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:07,800
People like Grandpa Bate

69
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,880
and Uncle Tuoka's farmlands

70
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,340
all grow goji berries.

71
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:13,640
But the best grower in our village

72
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:15,080
is Aunt Guli.

73
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:16,680
Under her leadership,

74
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:17,720
the goji berries in Xia Village

75
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:19,050
are of the best quality.

76
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:23,200
So I want to do something different

77
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:25,800
to maximize the value of the fresh berries.

78
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:27,600
Let me see.

79
00:03:28,079 --> 00:03:28,720
Okay.

80
00:03:29,160 --> 00:03:30,160
Help yourself if you want to eat more.

81
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:31,020
Move your foot.

82
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:34,560
What are you doing, Aunt Guli?

83
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:36,820
The roots of goji trees are very shallow.

84
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:38,640
The soil gets compacted easily.

85
00:03:39,079 --> 00:03:40,000
Step on this one too.

86
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,000
If that gets stepped on too,

87
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,079
how will my goji berries absorb

88
00:03:42,079 --> 00:03:43,400
water and nutrients?

89
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:44,280
Secretary,

90
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:46,200
are you here to date?

91
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:47,320
What

92
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:49,940
are you talking about?

93
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:51,360
This is the person I specially invited

94
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:53,480
to help Xia Village with our e-commerce business.

95
00:03:53,480 --> 00:03:54,560
Doing e-commerce?

96
00:03:55,079 --> 00:03:55,640
Right.

97
00:03:55,720 --> 00:03:57,840
You squatted at the door all night last night.

98
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:59,079
Tuoka saw it all.

99
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:02,920
Well,

100
00:04:03,160 --> 00:04:05,440
If you don't want people to step on the roots,

101
00:04:05,440 --> 00:04:07,480
you can set up a sign explaining why.

102
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:09,160
That way, people passing by the goji berry orchard

103
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:10,080
will all know.

104
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:11,720
You're right.

105
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:15,800
Then I'll bring you a sign tomorrow.

106
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:17,399
Don't push people like that again.

107
00:04:17,399 --> 00:04:18,160
Okay.

108
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:20,120
Miss, I was too anxious just now.

109
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:20,720
I'm sorry.

110
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:21,800
Sorry. It's fine.

111
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:23,040
You must be Aunt Guli.

112
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:23,880
Yes.

113
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:24,520
Hello.

114
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:25,840
Hello, I'm Ren Zhen.

115
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:26,760
I'm really here to

116
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:28,640
develop the live-streaming e-commerce business.

117
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:30,720
Your wolfberry farm is really great.

118
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:33,440
It's obvious that you've taken good care of it.

119
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:34,840
I'll have a lot of questions

120
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:35,920
to ask you in the future.

121
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:36,840
Okay, Miss.

122
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:37,720
No problem.

123
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:39,560
Secretary, she's a good girl.

124
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:42,120
Please don't mind her.

125
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:43,980
Aunt Guli is a really nice person.

126
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:46,280
She was just too worried about the wolfberries.

127
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:48,320
Let's help each other out next time.

128
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:49,920
Okay, Secretary.

129
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:51,960
Miss, if you want to eat fresh fruit in the future,

130
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:53,040
come to the farm to pick them.

131
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:53,560
Well,

132
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:55,560
pick them yourself,

133
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:56,690
and eat fresh fruit.

134
00:04:56,760 --> 00:04:57,200
Okay.

135
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:57,920
Thank you, Aunt Guli.

136
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:58,640
Okay.

137
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:05,320
Ulan.

138
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:08,600
Let me introduce you.

139
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:10,880
This is Ulan,

140
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:12,840
an employee of our cooperative.

141
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:13,800
This is Ren Zhen,

142
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:16,220
the head of our e-commerce business.

143
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:17,840
Hello.

144
00:05:18,440 --> 00:05:19,160
Hello.

145
00:05:19,880 --> 00:05:20,880
It's getting late.

146
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:22,680
Let's go eat at the cooperative.

147
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:23,600
Let's go.

148
00:05:29,880 --> 00:05:31,200
Wait for me!

149
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:22,840
Renzhen,

150
00:06:22,960 --> 00:06:25,020
these are all our Secretary's ideas.

151
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:26,570
Do you think they will sell?

152
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:29,650
He's really only been in office for three months.

153
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:33,800
No wonder he can be the Secretary.

154
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:35,920
Our Secretary

155
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,200
is an outstanding graduate of Peking University.

156
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:39,000
During campus recruitment,

157
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:41,040
several companies fought over him.

158
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:43,460
His starting salary was a million a year.

159
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:45,610
But our Secretary wasn't interested.

160
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:48,480
He said we have gold nuggets in Xia Village.

161
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:51,640
Although I haven't found them yet.

162
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:56,280
Is it possible that it's just a metaphor?

163
00:06:57,320 --> 00:06:58,240
A metaphor?

164
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:21,920
These are the contract-manufactured samples

165
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:22,880
from our county's company.

166
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:23,810
You can try some.

167
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:26,260
We're having Dapanji for dinner.

168
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:26,920
Okay.

169
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:30,970
What do you think

170
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:32,400
of the fresh goji berry products?

171
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:33,800
They look pretty decent.

172
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:35,680
If we add labels like green, healthy,

173
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:37,040
and NFC juice,

174
00:07:37,159 --> 00:07:38,560
many people will definitely buy them.

175
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:40,800
But things like the production line, logistics,

176
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:42,240
and output,

177
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:44,170
we can slowly optimize them later.

178
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:45,640
What we lack most right now

179
00:07:45,640 --> 00:07:47,040
is visibility.

180
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:49,650
Then we can do a livestream.

181
00:07:50,159 --> 00:07:52,620
It's not as simple as starting a livestream.

182
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:53,960
We need to build momentum.

183
00:07:53,960 --> 00:07:54,800
But Xiacun probably doesn't have a budget

184
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:56,800
for marketing and traffic, right?

185
00:07:57,640 --> 00:07:58,440
No.

186
00:08:00,320 --> 00:08:02,480
Then the most cost-effective way right now

187
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:04,000
is to run our own accounts

188
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:04,970
and post videos.

189
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:06,680
First, let more people see

190
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:09,280
that Xiacun has goji berries and fresh fruit products.

191
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:11,320
Let's get them interested first.

192
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:14,320
Then what content should we make for our accounts?

193
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:15,920
We can film anything in Xiacun.

194
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:17,680
Everything that grows and happens every day

195
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:18,940
can be filmed as a vlog.

196
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,840
Maybe we'll get a viral hit soon.

197
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:22,920
Or it might take half a year to a year.

198
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,480
But the team I led before

199
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:26,320
had a viral hit almost every month.

200
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:28,320
I have a lot of confidence in the cohesion

201
00:08:28,320 --> 00:08:29,920
and execution of Xia Village.

202
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:31,680
But in terms of work experience,

203
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:34,539
we definitely can't compare to your Hangzhou team.

204
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:38,919
Like she's never worked a day in her past life.

205
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:39,440
The CFO of Shangle Group takes all the credit.

206
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:40,520
Takes all the credit.

207
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:40,919
Last time, she worked herself to death,

208
00:08:40,919 --> 00:08:42,960
and made everyone else work themselves to death too.

209
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:44,760
Today she asked me for the live broadcast review.

210
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:45,080
I didn't give it.

211
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:45,240
So mad I could throw up, I didn't give it.

212
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:45,560
I didn't give it.

213
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:47,090
Can't be bothered with her.

214
00:08:47,680 --> 00:08:48,440
On the team-building list,

215
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:50,480
she even put me in the same room as her.

216
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:51,400
Is she crazy?

217
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:53,200
I'd rather pay to upgrade my room

218
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:54,660
than share a room with her.

219
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:56,400
Mr. Xiao, please transfer her away immediately.

220
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:57,280
Wrong group.

221
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:59,600
Quickly unsend it. Don't let her see it.

222
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:05,080
It's the same everywhere.

223
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:06,610
Don't worry, leave it to me.

224
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:14,920
This is my salary card.

225
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:15,880
It's yours to spend from now on.
